🔥 ✅ 2️⃣ Entitlement Processing (DEEP 🔥)
💡 Entitlement kya hai?
👉
Access / Permission / Group / Role

🧠 Simple example:-
External system (AD):-
john.doe → Groups:
- Admin
- HR

🔥 Step-by-step processing:-
🔹 Step 1: Fetch Entitlements
Account se groups nikalta hai.
Example:-
account.groups = [Admin, HR]

🔹 Step 2: Convert to IdentityIQ format
👉 System convert karta hai:-
Group → Managed Attribute.

🔹 Step 3: Link ke andar store hota hai
Link (account record) me save hota hai.

🔹 Step 4: Identity se attach hota hai
Identity → Entitlements assign.
🔥 Final Result
Identity: John
   ↓
Entitlements:
   - Admin
   - HR
-------
🧠 Real Example (AD):-
()AD user: john.doe
Groups: IT, Finance

()Aggregation ke baad:-
IdentityIQ:
Identity: John
Access:
   - IT
   - Finance
-------------
✅ 7️⃣ Deleted Accounts Check:-
Agar:-
checkDeleted = true

👉 To:-
✔ Jo account ab external system me nahi hai
✔ Unhe disable/delete mark karega

✅ 8️⃣ Full vs Delta Aggregation:-
🔥 Full:-
Sab accounts fetch honge
🔥 Delta:-
Sirf changed accounts fetch honge

👉 Based on:-
last aggregation time

✅ 9️⃣ Promotion (Optional):-
Account attributes → Identity attributes

✅ 🔟 Commit to Database
context.commitTransaction();

👉 Save hota hai:

✔ Identity
✔ Link
✔ Account data

